== Mashed Sweet Potatoes ==

Wash and dry produce (except green beans).

Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2
inches. Cover, bring to a boil, and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return sweet potatoes to pot. Add @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and ½ TBSP
@butter{3%tbsp}; mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Honey Butter ==

While sweet potatoes cook, place 2 TBSP butter in a #small microwave-safe bowl{};
microwave until softened, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Stir in @honey{2%tsp} and a pinch of salt.

== BBQ Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with salt
and pepper, then rub all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tbsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per
side.

> Swap in pork chops for chicken. Cook until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per
> side.

== Lemony Green Beans ==

While chicken cooks, pierce green bean bag with a fork; place bag on a #plate{}.
Microwave @green beans{6%oz} until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam green beans in a small pot with a splash of
> water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully transfer green beans to a #medium bowl{} and toss with lemon zest,
½ TBSP butter, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed sweet potatoes and green beans between plates. Top mashed sweet
potatoes with chicken. Dollop chicken with honey butter and sprinkle with
@chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.